<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO SPATZ</font><br>
<tt>Sat Nov 22 15:25:30 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Spatz,<br><br>
The debate ended when you started posting under false identities. <br><br>
Your use of &quot;et tu brute&quot; indicates a false assumption that you and I were on the same side. <br><br>
One interest I have is in educating students of the war. I receive requests all of the time from students, teachers, and other vets. They hear the good and the bad. Another interest is in helping other vets in any way that I can. <br><br>
You have self interest. How do I know? Because I compare you with the many people I have met who were against the war in Vietnam. None I have met are like you. You want a Memorial? You are building one for yourself right here on this site. You should be very proud.<br><br>
Me selling out? If one of my friends who were protestors told me that, it would probably bother me that they perceived me this way.<br><br>
But since it is you saying it, allow me to point out a couple of things.<br><br>
First, you have *sold out* the truth and the integrity of this site in order to enhance your own personal interests. Of course those voices in your ear keep telling you to persist, but you are foolishand you  listen to them. You stop at nothing. False postings and lies about laying down in front of trains.<br><br>
Another thing you need to know. I served in Vietnam with Conscientious Objectors. One's name was Art Combs. The first story I wrote about Vietnam was about how he went to the rescue of a Vietnamese child. My Lieutenant told me to drive to where Art and the child were. For all I knew at the time we were going through a mine field. We went anyway. We didn't get any medals for it, spatz. And there were none required. We were Americans helping a Vietnamese at a possible risk to ourselves. It is in self interest of Barry Spatz to maintain the viewpoint and the public stereotype that Americans were coldhearted 100% of the time in Vietnam. <br>
You will never be like Art Combs. Art Combs would never disgrace himself the way you do.<br><br>
You don't have a leg to stand on because you have nothing in common with us or with those who protested the war out of conscience.<br><br>

<p><code>-- wingman#greene.xtn..net  (Tom Dier) </code><p>


